<br>
Now, our server presents a problem, as you said, in that given the no-drop nature of the keys, it was possible for entire guilds to complete one key and get in.  However, unless they make an exception for our server alone, those on other servers that spend hours on end finishing those quests shouldn't be denied compensation just because of our unique server rules.<br>
<br>
Now, big question will be, how long do you have to get flagged for those zones before the reward is taken away? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=samildanachjownes>Samildanach Jownes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/11/03 11:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4458.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: rewards</span><hr size=1> The impression I get (and I could be wrong about this) is that it will still be possible to get the flags after the patch and in fact will still be required in many cases if you want to progress beyond these planes as quested flags aren't consider &quot;true&quot; flags in some cases. So, my guess is that you'll be able to get the proper flags and reward in the future too if you want. <br>
<br>
